<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36094e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36094e">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36094e"> 94(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Shun the fury</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;In the same week <font color="green">[2 November, 1641]</font> fifty-six Men, Women and Children, of the village of Bullogge (being frighted at what was done at Clontarff) took boats and went to sea, <mark>to shun the Fury</mark> of a party of Soldiers come out of Dublin, &hellip; but being pursued by the soldiers in other boats, were overtaken and thrown overboard.&rdquo; <font color="green">[Clarendon]</font> <small> Weston St. John Joyce, <a name="WSJ1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WSJ1"><cite title="source">The Neighbourhood of Dublin</cite></a> (1921) 28</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
